  <!-- HTML Section -->
  <div class="section active" id="html">
    <h2>1. HTML ‚Äî The Skeleton of Every Webpage</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <strong>What is HTML?</strong> <br>
      <b>HTML</b> stands for <b>H</b>yper<b>T</b>ext <b>M</b>arkup <b>L</b>anguage.<br>
      It's used to create the structure of web pages: headings, text, links, images, lists, forms, etc.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> Can you guess how a browser knows what to show on the page?<br>
      <b>Q:</b> What do you think <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> tags mean?
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Example: Simple HTML Page</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br>
&lt;html&gt;<br>
  &lt;head&gt;<br>
    &lt;title&gt;My First Page&lt;/title&gt;<br>
  &lt;/head&gt;<br>
  &lt;body&gt;<br>
    &lt;h1&gt;Hello, World!&lt;/h1&gt;<br>
    &lt;p&gt;This is my first web page.&lt;/p&gt;<br>
  &lt;/body&gt;<br>
&lt;/html&gt;
      </div>
      <div class="note">
        <ul>
          <li><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code> ‚Üí Tells browser: this is an HTML5 page.</li>
          <li><code>&lt;html&gt;</code> ‚Üí All the content goes inside.</li>
          <li><code>&lt;head&gt;</code> ‚Üí Info about the page (not visible).</li>
          <li><code>&lt;body&gt;</code> ‚Üí The visible part (what users see).</li>
          <li><code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> ‚Üí Heading 1 (biggest title).</li>
          <li><code>&lt;p&gt;</code> ‚Üí Paragraph (normal text).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Your "About Me" Page</b><br>
      Write a page about yourself!<br>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;<br>
&lt;html&gt;<br>
  &lt;head&gt;<br>
    &lt;title&gt;About Me&lt;/title&gt;<br>
  &lt;/head&gt;<br>
  &lt;body&gt;<br>
    &lt;h1&gt;My Name is [Your Name]&lt;/h1&gt;<br>
    &lt;p&gt;I am from Angul, Odisha.&lt;/p&gt;<br>
    &lt;p&gt;My hobbies: Coding, music, games.&lt;/p&gt;<br>
  &lt;/body&gt;<br>
&lt;/html&gt;
      </div>
      <b>Try changing:</b> Your name, hobbies, or add more paragraphs!
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Try This:</b> Add a heading about your favorite food and a paragraph explaining why you like it.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CSS Section -->
  <div class="section" id="css">
    <h2>2. CSS ‚Äî Make Your Page Beautiful</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <strong>What is CSS?</strong><br>
      <b>CSS</b> means <b>C</b>ascading <b>S</b>tyle <b>S</b>heets.<br>
      It adds color, style, and layout to your web page.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> What happens if you change the color in your CSS?<br>
      <b>Q:</b> How would you make your heading red?
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Example: Simple CSS Styling</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;style&gt;<br>
  body { background-color: #dff9fb; }<br>
  h1 { color: #eb4d4b; }<br>
  p { color: #30336b; font-size: 20px; }<br>
&lt;/style&gt;
      </div>
      <div class="note">
        <ul>
          <li><code>background-color</code> changes the page's background.</li>
          <li><code>color</code> changes text color.</li>
          <li><code>font-size</code> makes text bigger or smaller.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Style your "About Me" Page!</b><br>
      Add the <code>&lt;style&gt;</code> block in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> of your HTML.<br>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;style&gt;<br>
  body { background: #fffbe4; }<br>
  h1 { color: #d7263d; font-size: 36px; }<br>
  p { color: #1b262c; font-size: 22px; }<br>
&lt;/style&gt;
      </div>
      Make your page colorful!
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Try This:</b> Make one of your paragraphs blue. Make your heading bigger.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- JavaScript Section -->
  <div class="section" id="js">
    <h2>3. JavaScript ‚Äî Make Your Page Interactive</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <strong>What is JavaScript?</strong><br>
      <b>JavaScript</b> (JS) makes your web page interactive.<br>
      It can react when you click a button, type something, or move your mouse.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> How would you show a message when a button is clicked?
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Example: Change Text with a Button</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;h2 id="msg"&gt;Welcome!&lt;/h2&gt;<br>
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('msg').innerText = 'You clicked me!';"&gt;Click me&lt;/button&gt;
      </div>
      <div class="note">
        <ul>
          <li><code>id="msg"</code> ‚Üí Give a name to the heading.</li>
          <li><code>onclick="..."</code> ‚Üí Run JS code when button is clicked.</li>
          <li><code>document.getElementById('msg').innerText = ...</code> ‚Üí Change the text.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Color Changer</b><br>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;button onclick="document.body.style.backgroundColor = 'yellow';"&gt;Yellow&lt;/button&gt;<br>
&lt;button onclick="document.body.style.backgroundColor = 'lightblue';"&gt;Blue&lt;/button&gt;
      </div>
      <b>Try this:</b> Click the buttons to change the background color!
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Try This:</b> Make a button that makes your name appear or disappear!
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Example: Show/Hide Text</b>
      <div class="code-block">
&lt;p id="showme" style="display:none;"&gt;Hello, I am webTune1!&lt;/p&gt;<br>
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('showme').style.display='block';"&gt;Show Name&lt;/button&gt;<br>
&lt;button onclick="document.getElementById('showme').style.display='none';"&gt;Hide Name&lt;/button&gt;
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Python Section -->
  <div class="section" id="python">
    <h2>4. Python ‚Äî Code for Anything</h2>
    <div class="note">
      <strong>What is Python?</strong><br>
      <b>Python</b> is a powerful, easy-to-learn programming language.<br>
      You can't run Python in your browser, but you can install it on your computer and run in a terminal or code editor.
    </div>
    <div class="question">
      <b>Q:</b> Can you print your name using Python?
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Example: Print a Message</b>
      <div class="code-block">
print("Hello from Python!")
      </div>
      <div class="note">
        <code>print(...)</code> shows a message in your terminal.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="project">
      <b>Mini Project: Simple Calculator</b><br>
      <div class="code-block">
a = 10<br>
b = 5<br>
print("Sum:", a + b)<br>
print("Difference:", a - b)<br>
print("Product:", a * b)<br>
print("Quotient:", a / b)
      </div>
      <b>Try This:</b> Change <code>a</code> and <code>b</code> and see new results.
    </div>
    <div>
      <b>Practice:</b> Try writing a Python program to print your name and favorite food!
    </div>
    <div class="note">
      <b>How to run Python:</b>
      <ol>
        <li>Install Python from <a href="https://www.python.org/" target="_blank">python.org</a></li>
        <li>Open <b>Notepad</b> or <b>VS Code</b>, write your code, and save as <code>test.py</code></li>
        <li>Open <b>Command Prompt</b>, type: <code>python test.py</code></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </div>

